body_html: The crucial part of the documentation is "corresponding to the names in return_elements." To get the function to return some operations or tensors, you must specify a list names of operations or tensors. If you don't specify return_elements when calling tf.import_graph_def(), the function will return None.

body: The crucial part of the documentation is "corresponding to the names in `return_elements`." To get the function to return some operations or tensors, you must specify a list names of operations or tensors. If you don't specify `return_elements` when calling `tf.import_graph_def()`, the function will return `None`.
